13: Put me DOWN! I have to go back!
18:
You're not going anywhere until you
GET IT TOGETHER!
23:
This is no regular patrol. They must
have predicted we'd come here...
27:
Tch! We walked right into their
hands...
31:
Now the Starsayers are your
enemies too.
35:
Be glad you figured that out sooner
rather than later. Mishima, good
work.
49:
Do you want to know what all those
people down there have in common?
51:
They've seen what lies outside the
city. They also gained powers of
their own.
54:
You fall into both those categories.
Still feel like teaming up with the
Starsayers now?
59: Alk! Alk, can you hear me?
61:
We've got an emergency on our
hands! I can't get ahold of Stella
anymore!
65:
Your sister was with her before I lost
contact! You need to go back to the
shelter immediately!
69:
Why is it always one thing after
another!
74:
Remember—it's either us or the
Starsayers. You'll have to pick your
poison soon.
78:
Mishima, we're going to start
moving those people out of the
drainage area.
83:
Your powers will come in handy
here. If you want to save your
parents, you'll help us.
98:
As long as I can coordinate my
arms and legs to move separately.
103:
Seriously?! What about you, Mr.
Takamori? Can you fight?
115:
No way! How'd you dash around like
that?!
122:
N-no, I'm completely fine. Stella kept
me safe the whole time.
129:
Alk, we managed to connect
Starview Village to this world. The
gate is at the station.
134:
We should take your sister and
teacher to Starview, for their own
safety as well as our peace of mind.
148:
Ayumu, where are you going?
What's the rush?
150:
Safest place to be is here, y'know?
Especially now that I—
164:
Oh. I get it. You and her are trying to
ditch me, aren't you?
175:
You think I wouldn't notice? I'm not
as stupid as you both think I am!
177:
You only put up with me out of pity!
Well, guess what? I don't need your
PITY!
194:
I always hated your guts, right from
the get-go!
